Arthur: You can and will think what you want. That most certainly is your choice. I just try and write from my gut, not from smoke or mirrors, just from my gut. Sometimes clearly I have acid stomach and others times the content is calm. My thinking, like my emotions, bounce all over the place, and I don't mind who sees that. Even you.<br><br>
Slowly, from my own ups and downs I find learning and growth. That is purely selfish and for me. It also opens me up to understand others more, like the pain Silent Warrior expressed about standing on the tarmac, watching his friend crash, God, I could never imagine that, or the many others that I have been told here and via e mail.  Am I an emotional voyeur? Perhaps, but I don't think so. I just want to share feelings, and I have come to realize HOW MUCH MORE FEELINGS OTHERS HAVE than mine.  Took me awhile to realize that, and the humbling that came with it.  Meanwhile, you do what ever it is you do.<br><br>
Now what, Silent Warrior? Damn if I know. I am stunned by your intensity, and your experiences. If my thumb got hit by a hammer, and Ed's toe by a brick, what hit you, a cement truck or just a small nuke?  You're one helluva guy.<br><br>
